{title: Come And Dine}
{artist: Paul Williams}
{composer: Written by Charles B. Widmeyer}

[G]Jesus has a table spread
Where the [C]saints of God are fed
He [D7]invites His chosen people come and [G]dine
With His manna He doth feed
And [C]supplies our every need
Oh tis [D7]sweet to sup with Jesus all the [G]time
Come and [D7]dine the Master calleth come and [G]dine
You may [A7]feast at Jesus’ table all the [D7]time
He Who [G]fed the multitude turned the [C]water into wine
To the [D7]hungry calleth now come and [G]dine
The disciples came to land
Thus [C]obeying Christ’s command
For the [D7]Master called unto them come and [G]dine
There they found their heart’s desire
Bread and [C]fish upon the fire
Thus He [D7]satisfies the hungry every [G]time
Repeat #2
Soon the Lamb will take His bride
To be [C]ever at His side
All the [D7]host of heaven will assembled [G]be
Oh twill be a glorious sight
All the [C]robes is spotless white
And with [D7]Jesus they will feast eterna[G]lly
Repeat #2
Come and [C]dine come and [D7]dine come and [G]dine